<% content_for :title, "IMASUS App" %>

<main class="landing">
  <div class="landing__shell">
    <section class="landing__hero">
      <p class="landing__eyebrow">IMASUS Workshops</p>
      <h1 class="landing__title">Imagineering tools for students working on real-world challenges.</h1>
      <p class="landing__lead">
        IMASUS App is the workshop platform for students and facilitators developing new responses to large
        challenges through the imagineering approach inspired by Diane Nijs.
      </p>
      <div class="landing__actions">
        <a class="button button--primary" href="https://imasus.eu/" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">Visit IMASUS</a>
        <a class="button button--secondary" href="https://imasus.eu/blog/imagineering-expert-diane-nijs-interview/" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">Read the Imagineering Interview</a>
      </div>
      <p class="landing__status">Project foundation in progress</p>
    </section>

    <section class="landing__grid" aria-label="Project overview">
      <article class="landing__panel">
        <h2>Why this app exists</h2>
        <p>
          The application will support workshop journeys where students move from a broad challenge to structured
          reflection, concept development, and early solution framing.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="landing__panel">
        <h2>What is ready now</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Rails 8 foundation with PostgreSQL</li>
          <li>Munkit and Symphony workflow scaffolding</li>
          <li>Contributor guidance for a public repository</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="landing__panel">
        <h2>What comes next</h2>
        <p>
          The next product step is to define the first real workshop flow and the domain concepts that should anchor
          the student experience.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </div>
</main>
